    <img src="http://danfinlay.com/why-leaving-apple/img/consensys.svg">
    <p>I think of Consensys as a sort of digital cooperative, where its members are generally given free range to contribute to the community in whatever way they see fit.</p>
    <p>It's presently bankrolled by <a href="https://twitter.com/ethereumjoseph">Joseph Lubin</a>, who believes Ethereum has huge potential for mankind, and basically wants to stoke the flames.  You can listen to an interview on a podcast with him <a href="https://letstalkbitcoin.com/blog/post/the-ether-review-1-joseph-lubin">here</a>.</p>
    <p>Consensys is dedicated to generally promoting the creation of a more distributed internet. That means peer-to-peer, and less reliant on centralized authorities.</p>
    <img src="http://danfinlay.com/why-leaving-apple/img/networktypes.png">
    <p>There are a couple technologies at the heart of these efforts, most notably <a href="https://www.ethereum.org/">Ethereum</a> and <a href="https://ipfs.io/">IPFS</a></p>
